init_text: When you're 28, science discovers a drug that stops all effects of aging, creating immortality. Your government decides to give the drug to all citizens under 26, but you and the rest of the "Lost Generations" are deemed too high-risk. When you're 85, the side effects are finally discovered.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Those who took the drug are also reversing in age with no knowledge of what is happening and unable to influence with their life.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: wait for the dawn of the next day.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You hurry to your computer and fire it up.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You are living your life in hours instead of days.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: As the sun disappears below the horizon, you know your time has run out.
